key.substructure.key.doc.comment:
This protocol defines a generic constructs such that we can use DynamicGraph.AnyTensorGroup
to represent either a collection of tensors from multiple GPUs or one tensor.
It has a typed version DynamicGraph.TensorGroup to enforce type constraint.

key.doc.discussion.Para: A model builder on the other hand doesnt have that restriction. When input changes, it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way, you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components (parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesnt reset your training. This also means you need to make sure parameter shape wont change when input changes, otherwise we will fatal.
